HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 284
BY REPRESENTATIVE SPELL
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH: Designates May 22, 2026, as World Preeclampsia
Awareness Day in Louisiana
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Wednesday, May 22, 2026, as World Preeclampsia Awareness Day in
3 Louisiana.
4 WHEREAS, May is recognized nationally and internationally as Preeclampsia
5 Awareness Month and aims to increase understanding of this life-threatening hypertensive
6 disorder of pregnancy; and
7 WHEREAS, World Preeclampsia Day is observed annually on May twenty-second
8 to raise global awareness of preeclampsia, a serious pregnancy-related condition that poses
9 significant risks to maternal and infant health; and
10 WHEREAS, preeclampsia is most often characterized by a rapid rise in blood
11 pressure that can lead to seizure, stroke, multiple organ failure, and the death of the mother
12 and baby; and
13 WHEREAS, the United States currently ranks forty-seventh worldwide for maternal
14 mortality and is the only industrialized nation with a rising maternal mortality rate; and
15 WHEREAS, in the United States, preeclampsia complicates approximately one in
16 every twenty-five pregnancies; and
17 WHEREAS, in 2024, Louisiana recorded a maternal mortality rate of 41.9 deaths per
18 one hundred thousand live births, which is the highest rate in the nation; and
19 WHEREAS, according to America's Health Rankings, 18.3 percent of Louisiana
20 women between the ages of eighteen and forty-four have been diagnosed with high blood
21 pressure, placing Louisiana forty-sixth among all states; and
