1 WHEREAS, sixty percent of hypertension-related maternal deaths are considered
2 potentially preventable with timely diagnosis, treatment, and coordinated care; and
3 WHEREAS, maternal death has profound and lasting emotional, social, and
4 economic impacts on families and communities throughout Louisiana; and
5 WHEREAS, the primary treatment for preeclampsia involves early delivery of the
6 infant to prevent disease progression and complications; and
7 WHEREAS, in 2024, Louisiana ranked fifty-first among the fifty states and Puerto
8 Rico for premature births, and preeclampsia is recorded as a significant contributing factor
9 to such births; and
10 WHEREAS, Louisiana continues to rank among the states with the highest infant
11 mortality rates in the United States, with nine deaths per one thousand live births compared
12 to the national average of 5.6, according to America's Health Rankings; and
13 WHEREAS, it is imperative that Louisiana address the prevalence of infant and
14 maternal mortality in the state and work to provide more effective care for the state's
15 expecting mothers and unborn children.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
17 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Wednesday, May 22, 2026, as World
18 Preeclampsia Awareness Day in Louisiana and does hereby acknowledge Woman's Hospital
19 for providing care to pregnant women to help reduce maternal and infant deaths and reduce
20 the number of pre-term births.
